The '''A339''' is a {{convert|32|mi|km|adj=mid|-long}} [[Great Britain road numbering scheme|A road]] in [[England]]. It is the main road between [[Newbury, Berkshire|Newbury]] in [[Berkshire]] and [[Alton, Hampshire|Alton]] in [[Hampshire]]. It also forms the eastern and northern parts of the [[Basingstoke, Hampshire|Basingstoke]] Ring Road. Its most northern end eventually merges into the A34 north of [[Newbury, Berkshire|Newbury]] just before meeting the [[M4 motorway|M4]] at J13 ([[Chieveley services]]).

