{{Infobox Political post |post = Head of Government |body = Tokelau |insignia = Badge of Tokelau.svg |insigniasize = 100px |insigniacaption = Badge of Tokelau |termlength = |image = |imagesize = |incumbent = [[Afega Gaualofa]] |incumbentsince = 5 March 2018 |appointer = |formation = February 1993 |inaugural = [[Salesio Lui]] |website = }} {{Politics of Tokelau}}
The office of '''head of government of Tokelau''' (''Ulu-o-Tokelau''), often simply called the ''Ulu'',<ref name=rnzi>{{cite news |first=|last=|title=Tokelau ulu keen to restore wide consultation |url=http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=49113|work=[[Radio New Zealand International]]|publisher=|date=15 September 2009 |accessdate=15 September 2009}}</ref> rotates yearly between the ''faipule'' (leaders) of [[Tokelau]]'s three [[atolls]] - [[Atafu]], [[Fakaofo]], and [[Nukunonu]]. The current Ulu is [[Afega Gaualofa]], the Faipule of [[Fakaofo]] atoll, who has held the position since March 2018.
There have been 26 ''Ulus of Tokelau'' since 1993, when the office was established, and 2018.<ref name=pg/><ref name=pir>{{cite news |first=|last=|title=Tokelau Inaugurates New Ulu Siopili Perez |url=http://www.pireport.org/articles/2017/03/07/tokelau-inaugurates-new-ulu-siopili-perez |work=[[Radio New Zealand International]] |publisher=Pacific Islands Reports |date=2017-03-07 |accessdate=2017-07-14}}</ref>
