{{SaoTomePrincipe-geo-stub}}

'''Jens Christian Hansen''' (5 May 1932 in [[Bodø]] – 8 May 2014) was a Norwegian geographer.
He took the [[dr.philos.]] degree in 1970 with the thesis ''Administrative grenser og tettstedsvekst''. After a period as a [[docent]] at the [[Norwegian School of Economics]] he was a professor at the [[University of Bergen]] from 1972. He was a fellow of the [[Norwegian Academy of Science and Letters]] from 1985, of the [[Academia Europaea]]<ref>[http://www.ae-info.org/ae/User/Hansen_Jens_Christian Academia Europaea membership profile]. Retrieved 11 June 2014.</ref> and of the [[Royal Norwegian Society of Sciences and Letters]]. He died in May 2014.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Jens Christian Hansen|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=|location=|url=http://www.snl.no/Jens_Christian_Hansen|language=Norwegian|accessdate=4 June 2014}}</ref>
