| colspan="3"|{{small|{{legend|#f99|''indicates a single day record, single weekend record, single week record, or cumulative gross record.''<ref name="singleday" /><ref name="Opening_Weekends" /><ref name="OW" /><ref name=":1" />|text={{dagger}}}}{{legend|#99f|''indicates a day of the week record or non-opening weekend record.''<ref name="Sundays" /><ref name="mondays" /><ref name="tuesdays" /><ref name="2ndweekends" /><ref name="3rdweekends" />|text={{double-dagger}}}}{{legend|#ddf|''indicates a non-opening day of the week record.''<ref name="NonOpeningWednesday" />|text={{hash-tag}}}}''All of the cumulative grosses were records within their time frame.''}}
|}
In the domestic market, the film grossed more money faster than any previous film. It set several records for specific time frames and days of the week, including ones that were still records when adjusting for inflation. Many of the records it broke were set by ''[[Jurassic World]]'', which was released six months prior in June 2015.
