*Northernmost point &ndash; [[Out Stack]], [[Shetland]] at {{coord|60|51|N|0|52|W|region:GB-ZET_type:landmark}}
*Northernmost settlement &ndash; [[Skaw, Unst]], Shetland Islands at {{coord|60|49|N|0|47|W|region:GB-ZET_type:city}}
*Southernmost point &ndash; [[Pednathise Head]], [[Western Rocks, Isles of Scilly|Western Rocks]], [[Isles of Scilly]] at {{coord|49|51|N|6|24|W|region:GB-IOS_type:landmark}}
*Southernmost settlement &ndash; [[St Agnes, Isles of Scilly|St Agnes]], Isles of Scilly at {{coord|49|53|N|6|20|W|region:GB-IOS_type:city}}
*Westernmost point &ndash; [[Rockall]] at {{coord|57|35|N|13|41|W|region:GB_type:landmark}}, which was only incorporated into Scotland in the 20th century.  If Rockall is ignored, [[Soay, St Kilda|Soay]], [[St Kilda, Scotland|St Kilda]], at {{coord|57.830|-8.638|region:GB_type:landmark}} is the westernmost point.
*Westernmost settlement &ndash; [[Belleek, County Fermanagh|Belleek]], [[County Fermanagh]] at {{coord|54|28|N|8|9.8|W|region:GB-FER_type:city}}. Until 1930, the westernmost settlement was [[Hirta]], on the island of [[St Kilda, Scotland|St Kilda]], but it is now abandoned; the island now has a military base, staffed during the summer months.
*Easternmost point &ndash; [[Ness Point|Lowestoft Ness]], [[Suffolk]], at {{coord|52|29|N|1|46|E|region:GB-SFK_type:landmark}}
*Easternmost settlement &ndash; [[Lowestoft]], Suffolk, at {{coord|52|28|N|1|45|E|region:GB-SFK_type:city}}
*Highest point &ndash; [[Ben Nevis]], [[Scotland]], at 1345 m {{coord|56.797|-5.004|region:GB_type:mountain}}
*Lowest point &ndash; [[Holme Fen]], [[Cambridgeshire]], 3 m below sea level at {{coord|52|29|N|0|13|W|region:GB-CAM_type:landmark}}
