After a brief period of political turmoil, a survivor of the Koala ruling family, Kalinkuma, established a new town of Koala (at its present location) as the capital of a second kingdom of that name.{{sfn|Madiéga|1982|pp=131–132}} Although the title of ''bedo'' was retained by the local traditional ruler even after the French occupation of the region, this second kingdom occupied a substantially smaller territory and had relatively little regional influence.{{sfn|Madiéga|1982|pp=133–135}}

