==Prior to 20th century== {{History_of_Albania}}
* 1572 - Tirana mentioned as "Borgo di Tirana" - Tirana-[[Burgh#Etymology|burgh]].<ref>{{citation|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zHxsWspxGIIC&pg=PA451&dq=borgo+di+tirana&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CBwQ6AEwAGoVChMIvabkqa2ayQIVRj8-Ch0cRwyc#v=onepage&q=borgo%20di%20tirana&f=false|page=451| title=Islamic Desk Reference|author=E. J. Van Donzel|quote="il borgo di Tirana" is already mentioned as early as 1572|publisher=E.J. Brill|year=1994|isbn=9780585305561|oclc=45731063}}</ref> * 1614 - [[Sulejman Bargjini]] built a [[Turkish bath|hammam]], bakery, and [[mosque]], transforming the settlement into a commercial center of the area.<ref name="Elsie2010">{{cite book|author= Robert Elsie |title=Historical Dictionary of Albania|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=haFlGXIg8uoC|year= 2010 |edition=2nd |publisher=[[Scarecrow Press]]|isbn=978-0-8108-7380-3}}</ref> * 1780 - [[Saint Procopius Church of Tirana]] established.<ref name=Historia /> * 1822 - [[Et'hem Bey Mosque]]<ref name="Elsie2010" /> and [[Clock Tower of Tirana]]<ref name=Historia /> built. * 1865 ** Municipal Council created (approximate date).{{sfn|Kera|2009}} ** St. Mary's Catholic Church built.<ref name=Historia />
==20th century==
* 1912 - 26 November: The Albanian flag is raised, two days before the [[Albanian Declaration of Independence]] in [[Vlorë|Valona]].<ref>{{citation| url=http://ibrahimdalliu.edu.al/hafiz-ibrahim-dalliu-patriot-dhe-atdhetar/| language=Albanian| title=Hafiz Ibrahim Dalliu, patriot dhe atdhetar | quote=Më 26 nëntor 1912 është pjesëmarrës aktiv në përgatitjen dhe zhvillimin e ceremonisë së ngritjes së Flamurit dhe shpalljes së pavarësisë në Tiranë.|publisher=Shkolla Jopublike Hafiz Ibrahim Dalliu}}</ref> * 1913 - [[Zyber Hallulli]] becomes mayor. * 1917 - 28 November: "Streha Vorfnore", the first public [[orphanage]] in Albania was established.<ref name="Lika">{{citation|publisher=peshkupauje.com| author=Ferit Lika| language=Albanian| accessdate=2014-01-18| title="Streha Vorfnore", misioni i (pa) ndërprerë në këto 100 vjet|trans-title="Streha Vorfnore", an uniterrupted mission in these 100 years| date=2013-01-16}}</ref> * 1918 - 19–20 December: [[Congress of Tirana, 1918|Congress of Tirana]] took place, a preparatory for the [[Congress of Durrës]].<ref>{{cite book| title=Albania in the Twentieth Century, A History: Volume I: Albania and King Zog, 1908–39|author=Owen Pearson| isbn=978-1-84511-013-0 |publisher=I. B. Tauris | date=February 2, 2006| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3_Sh3y9IMZAC&pg=PA117&lpg=PA117&dq=luigj+bumci&source=bl&ots=btPsxvCswb&sig=_0BV_ItBZHQBHu-250l3N86PZOY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=yD2vUuXBL-KpsATC7oHoBA&ved=0CGUQ6AEwDA#v=onepage&q=luigj%20bumci&f=false| accessdate=2013-12-16 |pages=115–116}}</ref> * 1920 - 9 February: Tirana becomes provisional capital of Albania.<ref name="Elsie2010" /><ref name=Historia>{{cite web |url=http://www.tirana.gov.al/sq/Historia-e-Tiranes1 |title=Historia e Tiranës |trans-title=History of Tirana |work= Tirana.gov.al |language=Albanian |publisher=Bashkia Tiranë (Municipality of Tirana) |accessdate=30 November 2015 }} (includes timeline)</ref> * 1921 - Albanian Vocational School founded.<ref name="Vickers1995">{{cite book|author= Miranda Vickers |title=The Albanians: A Modern History|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QnYAAwAAQBAJ|year= 1995|publisher=I.B.Tauris|isbn=978-0-85771-025-3}}</ref> * 1922 - National Library headquartered in Tirana.<ref name="Library1993">{{cite book|title=World Encyclopedia of Library and Information Services|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HSFu99FCJwQC|year= 1993|publisher=American Library Association|isbn=978-0-8389-0609-5 |chapter=Albania |page=40+ |author=[[Mahir Domi]]}}</ref> * 1923 - [[Muslim Community of Albania]] headquartered in Tirana. * 1925 **[[Bektashi order]] moved its headquarters in Tirana.<ref>{{citation| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7WS1CgAAQBAJ&pg=PT131&dq=bektashi+moved+to+tirana+1925&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCIQ6AEwAWoVChMIg-zyuq-ayQIVwoI-Ch3l-AD4#v=onepage&q=bektashi%20moved%20to%20tirana%201925&f=false| title=Shi'I Islam: A Beginner's Guide| author=Moojan Momen|quote=Mustafa Atatürk banned all Sufi orders in 1925 and the order moved its headquarters to Tirana in Albania| year=2015| publisher=London Oneworld Publications|isbn=9781780747873 |oclc=927509799}}</ref> **31 December: Tirana becomes permanent capital of Albania.<ref name=Historia /> * 1926 - 27 November: Italian-Albanian {{Interlanguage link multi|Pact of Tirana|de|3=Tiranapakt|lt=pact}} signed in Tirana.<ref name="Elsie2010" /> * 1927 - 22 November: Italian-Albanian military {{Interlanguage link multi|Pact of Tirana|de|3=Tiranapakt|lt=pact}} signed in Tirana.<ref name="Elsie2010" /> * 1929 - [[Orthodox Autocephalous Church of Albania]] headquartered in Tirana.<ref name=europa2003>{{cite book|title=Europa World Year Book 2003|year= 2003|publisher=[[Europa Publications]] |isbn=978-1-85743-227-5 |chapter=Albania |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XLvU9lroRuUC |page=438+ }}</ref> * 1930 - [[Dëshmorët e Kombit Boulevard]] laid out.<ref name=Historia /> * 1938 - [[Radio Tirana]] begins broadcasting.<ref name="Elsie2010" /> * 1939 ** Italian occupation begins.<ref name="Elsie2010" /> ** Kosovo cinema opens. * 1941 - [[Party of Labour of Albania|Communist Party of Albania]] headquartered in Tirana. * 1942 - ''[[Zëri i Popullit]]'' newspaper begins publication.<ref name=europa2003 /> * 1943 ** Italian occupation ends.<ref name="Elsie2010" /> ** ''[[Bashkimi (Democratic Front newspaper)|Bashkimi]]'' newspaper begins publication. * 1945 - [[National Theater of Albania|State Professional Theatre]] active.<ref name=rubin1994>{{cite book |title=World Encyclopedia of Contemporary Theatre: Europe |editor= Don Rubin |year=1994 |publisher=Routledge|isbn=9780415251570 |chapter=Albania |page= 35+ |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=klGvBAAAQBAJ }}</ref> * 1946 - Teachers' college opens.<ref name="Shaffer1967">{{cite book|editor=[[Harry G. Shaffer]] |title=The Communist World: Marxist and Non-Marxist Views |year=1967|publisher= [[Appleton-Century-Crofts]] |location=New York |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=h9FFVgu-Ff0C |chapter= People's Republic of Albania: an Albanian Marxist View |pages=382–404 }}</ref> * 1949 - [[Durrës]]-Tirana railway begins operating.<ref name="Elsie2010" /> * 1950 - [[Rinia Park]] created. * 1951 - [[Agricultural University of Tirana|Higher Agricultural Institute]] established. * 1953 - [[National Theatre of Opera and Ballet of Albania]] founded. * 1954 - [[National Art Gallery of Albania|Gallery of Figurative Art]] opens.<ref name="Elsie2010" /> * 1957 - [[University of Tirana|State University of Tirana]] established.<ref name="Ruegg2011">{{cite book|editor=Walter Rüegg |editor-link=Walter Rüegg |series=History of the University in Europe |volume=4 |title= Universities Since 1945 |year=2011|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-139-49425-0 |chapter= Universities founded in Europe between 1945 and 1995 |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=VCKRv1GiFqEC |page=575+ }}</ref> * 1960 - Great Park created.{{sfn|Felstehausen|1999}} * 1963 - [[Palace of Culture of Tirana]] built.<ref name=Historia /> * 1966 - [[Academy of Arts in Tirana|High Institute of Arts]] founded. * 1968 - [[Skanderbeg Monument]] erected in [[Skanderbeg Square]].<ref name=Historia /> * 1971 - University's [[Botanical Gardens of Tirana]] created.<ref name=botanic>{{cite web |url= http://www.bgci.org/garden_search.php?action=Find&ftrCountry=AL |title=Garden Search: Albania |publisher= [[Botanic Gardens Conservation International]] |location=London |accessdate= 30 November 2015 }}</ref> * 1972 - [[Academy of Sciences of Albania]] headquartered in city.<ref name="Elsie2010" /> * 1979 - Population: 189,000. * 1981 - [[National Historical Museum (Albania)]] opens.<ref name=Historia /> * 1986 - [[Palace of Congresses]] built. * 1988 ** [[Pyramid of Tirana|International Center of Culture]] opens.<ref name=Historia /> ** {{Interlanguage link multi|Enver Hoxha statue|sq|3=Monumenti i Enver Hoxhës në Tiranë}} erected. * 1989 - Population: 238,057. * 1990 - December: Student strike.<ref name="Schmidt1992">{{cite book|editor=Joan Campbell|title=European Labor Unions|year= 1992|publisher=Greenwood |isbn=978-0-313-26371-2 |chapter=Albania |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=23dUzlVxphMC |author=Michael Schmidt-Neke |author-link=:de:Michael Schmidt-Neke }}</ref> * 1991 ** ''[[Koha Jonë]]'' newspaper begins publication.<ref name=europa2003 /> ** [[Polytechnic University of Tirana]] active.<ref name="Ruegg2011" /> ** [[Confederation of Trade Unions (Albania)]] headquartered in Tirana.<ref name="Schmidt1992" /> * 1992 - Prefecture of Tirana created.{{sfn|Pojani|2010}} * 1997 - January: [[Albanian Rebellion of 1997]] begins. * 2000 - Design of [[Symbols of Tirana|Tirana Coat of Arms]] adopted.
==21st century==
* 2008 - 10 March: [[Centre of Albanological Studies]] established.<ref>[http://qsa.edu.al/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=47&Itemid=241&lang=sq History of CAS (in Albanian)]</ref> * 2001 ** [[St Paul's Cathedral (Tirana)]] built. ** Population: 343,078.<ref name=europa2003 /> * 2011 ** January: [[2011 Albanian opposition demonstrations]].<ref name="bbc-chron">{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-17681099 |work=BBC News |title= Albania Profile: Timeline |accessdate= 30 November 2015 }}</ref> ** 8 May: [[Albanian local elections, 2011]] held. ** [[Lulzim Basha]] becomes mayor. ** Population: 418,495.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/dyb2.htm |work=Demographic Yearbook 2013 |publisher=[[United Nations Statistics Division]] |title=Population of Capital Cities and Cities of 100,000 or More Inhabitants }}</ref> * 2012 ** [[Resurrection Cathedral, Tirana]] built. ** [[TID Tower]] built (approximate date).{{citation needed|date=November 2015}} * 2015 - [[Erion Veliaj]] becomes mayor.
